subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitat.
Lowland to hill dipterocarp rainforest (Mount Kinabalu). Elevational range is sea level to ¢.1000 m, with occasional records to 1600 m (e.g. Crocker Range) and possibly higher. Hose’s Langurs occasionally enter plantations. They are sympatric with the Maroon Langur (
P. rubicunda
) in the northern part of their distribution, the Crossmarked Langur (
P. chrysomelas
) in the western part, and the White-fronted Langur (
P. frontata
) elsewhere; but one or the other at any locality is absent or rare.
